  "guidance": [
    {
      "type": "Change From Last Year",
      "text": "Revised question dependency",
      "typeKo": "전년 대비 변경사항",
      "textKo": "Revised 문항 의존도"
    },
    {
      "type": "Question Dependencies",
      "text": "This question only appears if you select \"Yes\" in response to column 1 \"Emissions reduction initiatives that were active within the reporting year\" in 7.55",
      "typeKo": "문항 의존성",
      "textKo": "- 이 문항은 선행 문항의 응답에 따라 표시 여부 또는 입력 범위가 달라질 수 있습니다. - 선행 문항의 응답을 수정하면 이 문항 또는 후속 문항의 기존 입력값이 초기화될 수 있으므로 제출 전 함께 확인하십시오."
    },
    {
      "type": "Requested Content",
      "text": "General \nThis question is intended to gather information on the ways in which capital is directed towards emissions reduction activities within your organization's value chain (i.e. Scope 1, Scope 2 and/or Scope 3), and/or the way in which initiatives are identified. If your organization uses an internal carbon price you are encouraged to report this here in addition to in module 5 \"Business strategy\" section \"Pricing Environmental Externalities\".\nMethod \n(column 1) \nSelect the types of methods that you employ to help to channel funds towards emissions reduction initiatives.\nComment (column 2) (optional) \nProvide additional details or examples as necessary.",
      "typeKo": "요청 내용",
      "textKo": "- 응답방법과 열 구조에 따라 해당 배출량, 에너지, 목표 또는 성과 지표를 입력하십시오. - 수치는 문항에서 요구하는 단위와 보고연도 기준을 일관되게 적용하십시오. - 산정에 사용한 방법론, 배출계수, 제외 범위 또는 추정 기준이 있다면 설명 입력란에 근거를 남기십시오."
    },
    {
      "type": "Additional Information",
      "text": "Marginal Abatement Cost Curves \nMarginal Abatement Cost Curves, or MACCs, provide a method of evaluating potential emissions reduction activities. They provide a visual comparison of the marginal abatement costs for different projects.\nMACCs can be generated to evaluate options at any level of organization - from individual business divisions, to the overall business and to sectors and countries/areas, evaluating individual projects, programs or policies.\nMarginal abatement costs are calculated by dividing the costs of the project (calculated from the initial cost minus any savings made as a result of the project) by the greenhouse gas emissions saved over a specified investment timeframe.\nThese are then arranged with the lowest costs (sometime negative cost) on the left, increasing in cost to the right, creating the curve. An example taken from McKinsey & Company \" Impact of the financial crisis on carbon economics: Version 2.1 of the global greenhouse gas abatement cost curve \" \nThose projects/initiatives where there are cost savings to be made over the lifetime of the project as a result of the emissions savings made, and therefore, even without a commitment to carbon reduction investment, should be implemented from a cost saving point of view. Where positive costs are associated with the proposals the MACC curve can be used to suggest the lowest cost options for achieving a particular target ( McKinsey & Company, 2010 , page 8).\nAs with all evaluation methods, the accuracy of the MACC will depend on that of the input data.",
      "typeKo": "추가 정보",
      "textKo": "이 섹션은 응답 작성 시 참고할 수 있는 추가 설명입니다. 필요한 경우 관련 기준, 방법론, 내부 검토 자료 또는 외부 근거자료를 함께 확인하십시오."
    }
  ],
